# ms178-1.patch v8 (2026-07-22)
# Target: vkd3d-proton origin/master 3dfc6f07d0953b1e8b41705275c2c59cc7374fc5
#
# v8 retains every existing v7 functional hunk, including the reviewed
# direct-queue barrier-layout fix from PR #3161, and adds upstream PR #3155:
#
#   vkd3d: Be a bit more nuanced in how we do image suballocation.
#   upstream commit f3f0cc4902a8070f6990c4714c0353809b536f38
#
# Reviewed policy:
# - Default committed-texture suballocation is retained. This follows the
#   measured Diablo IV CPU regression caused by frequent committed textures.
# - On drivers supporting both zero-initialized device memory and pageable
#   device-local memory, dedicated image allocations remain the default so
#   dynamic memory priorities remain useful.
# - disallow_committed_texture_suballocation only selects dedicated committed
#   textures where that capability combination makes it meaningful.
# - allow_image_heap_suballocation is an explicit Tier-2 override.
#
# No unproven shader, descriptor-copy, synchronization, cache, or queue change
# was introduced while integrating the upstream MR.
#
# Initialize nested submodules before application:
#   git submodule update --init --recursive
#   patch -p1 -i ms178-1.patch
#
